laboratory_examinations.findings: Elevated levels of CK (20,232 U/L), alanine aminotransferase (208 U/L), aspartate aminotransferase (190.5 U/L), and lactate dehydrogenase (647 U/L)
Myopathic pattern in the right vastus lateralis and deltoid muscle, suggestive of primary muscle disease
Extensive loss of skeletal muscle fibers that were replaced by fat tissue and extensive fibrosis noted
